	CHAPTER 1. THE POLITICAL ECONOMY OF AN FTA
	The FTA as the rallying point of a new political labor 
	initiative. Labor has positioned itself in combination with a 
	number of issues oriented groups (wildlife, toxic substances, 
	human rights etc.) to fight an FTA. The administration and 
	business strongly favor it. Is there a bargain to be struck 
	involving broader issues including safety standards and 
	environmental issues? 
	
