       protection in key areas where the United States can as a result 
       expect to score export growth. This includes specifically 
       electronic equipment, automotive products, steel and textiles. In 
       the automobile industry a major restructuring could be expected, 
       though not one that would harm the United States.3 The US textile 
       sector is an example of an industry that has already demonstrated 
